{
  "texts": [
    "As presented in Table 1, crash parameters are imported from three sources: Signal4Analytics, RITIS Traffic Data, and RITIS Event Data.",
    "Signal4Analytics (S4A) is a statewide web-based interactive crash mapping and analysis system.",
    "In the crash data, contributing factors that are associated with crash occurrences in previous studies, such as speeding-related crashes, are considered.",
    "Traffic and event data are collected through RITIS (Regional Integrated Transportation Information System), a situational awareness, data archiving, and analytics platform used by transportation officials (49).",
    "The traffic data includes variables such as speed, traffic volume, and occupancy, which are aggregated on a segment basis."
  ]
}